```
- one
- two
.
<ul>
<li>
one
</li>
<li>
two
</li>
</ul>
```

Sublists can interrupt single-line items without a blank line.

```
- one
 - two
  - three
.
<ul>
<li>
one
<ul>
<li>
two
<ul>
<li>
three
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
```

```
- one

 - two

  - three
.
<ul>
<li>
one
<ul>
<li>
two
<ul>
<li>
three
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
```

```
- one
  and

  another paragraph

  - a list

- two
.
<ul>
<li>
<p>one
and</p>
<p>another paragraph</p>
<ul>
<li>
a list
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p>two</p>
</li>
</ul>
```

```
- one
lazy
- two
.
<ul>
<li>
one
lazy
</li>
<li>
two
</li>
</ul>
```

```
- a
- b
+ c
.
<ul>
<li>
a
</li>
<li>
b
</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>
c
</li>
</ul>
```

```
- a

- b
.
<ul>
<li>
<p>a</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>b</p>
</li>
</ul>
```

Sublist without blank line; inner list is loose (blank line between b and c).

```
- a
  - b

  - c
- d
.
<ul>
<li>
a
<ul>
<li>
<p>b</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>c</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
d
</li>
</ul>
```

Same, but outer list stays tight (no blank between a-group and d in the
outer list's items — the blank line before d closes the inner list's item,
not the outer list's item).

```
- a
  - b

  - c

- d
.
<ul>
<li>
a
<ul>
<li>
<p>b</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>c</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
d
</li>
</ul>
```

```
- a

  b
- c
.
<ul>
<li>
<p>a</p>
<p>b</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>c</p>
</li>
</ul>
```

