When ambiguous, prioritize roman numerals.

```
i. a
i. b
.
<ol type="i">
<li>
a
</li>
<li>
b
</li>
</ol>
```

```
I. a
II. b
E. d
.
<ol type="I">
<li>
a
</li>
<li>
b
</li>
</ol>
<ol start="5" type="A">
<li>
d
</li>
</ol>
```

```
The civil war ended in
1865. And this should not start a list.
.
<p>The civil war ended in
1865. And this should not start a list.</p>
```

Sublist interruption rule: a block-level element can interrupt a list
item only if the item has no continuation lines yet.

Single-line item immediately followed by a sublist.

```
- foo
  - bar
.
<ul>
<li>
foo
<ul>
<li>
bar
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
```

Multi-line item: sublist without blank line is treated as continuation.

```
- foo
  bar
  - baz
.
<ul>
<li>
foo
bar
- baz
</li>
</ul>
```

Three levels of nesting, each item single-line.

```
- a
  - b
    - c
.
<ul>
<li>
a
<ul>
<li>
b
<ul>
<li>
c
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
```

Blockquote interrupts a single-line list item.

```
- foo
  > bar
.
<ul>
<li>
foo
<blockquote>
bar
</blockquote>
</li>
</ul>
```

Blockquote blocked by continuation lines.

```
- foo
  bar
  > baz
.
<ul>
<li>
foo
bar
&gt; baz
</li>
</ul>
```

Mixed ordered and unordered sublists.

```
- foo
  1. bar
.
<ul>
<li>
foo
<ol>
<li>
bar
</li>
</ol>
</li>
</ul>
```

Lazy continuation counts as a continuation line, blocking sublist.

```
- foo
bar
  - baz
.
<ul>
<li>
foo
bar
- baz
</li>
</ul>
```

Multi-line item with blank line then sublist (still works via blank line).

```
- foo
  bar

  - sub
.
<ul>
<li>
foo
bar
<ul>
<li>
sub
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
```

Tight sublist (no blank lines between sub-items).

```
- a
  - b
  - c
.
<ul>
<li>
a
<ul>
<li>
b
</li>
<li>
c
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
```
